n  |             --------- move occurs because `bytes` has type `std::string::String`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait\r\n4 |         bar(&mut bytes);\r\n  |             ^^^^^^^^^^ value borrowed here after move\r\n5 |         println!(\"{}\", bytes);\r\n6 |     }\r\n  |     - value moved here, in previous iteration of loop\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n<!--\r\nIf you're using the stable version of the compiler, you should also check if the\r\nbug also exists in the beta or nightly versions.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.43.0-nightly (6d69caba1 2020-02-27)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: 6d69caba110c0c2fb90180df1cbc8be5033b91d4\r\ncommit-date: 2020-02-27\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.43.0-nightly\r\nLLVM version: 9.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!--\r\nInclude a backtrace in the code block by setting `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` in your\r\nenvironment. E.g. `RUST_BACKTRACE=1 cargo build`.\r\n-->\r\n<details><summary>Backtrace</summary>\r\n<p>\r\n\r\nNot applicable, since code doesn't compile.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n</details>\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69536/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/69536/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}